The paper deals with graph algorithms and specifically kernelization algorithms for the Dominating Set and Connected Dominating Set problems on graphs with excluded topological subgraphs. This falls under the categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Graph Theory (cs.GT), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). However, since the paper focuses on graph algorithms and kernelization, cs.DM and cs.DS are the most likely categories, followed by cs.CG and cs.GT, and finally cs.CC due to the complexity analysis of the algorithms.
